  "script": "A great white shark circled a small fishing boat for hours, and the people on board caught the whole thing on camera. The shark, easily longer than the boat itself, kept gliding past just under the surface, bumping the hull and rolling an eye up at the crew. Great whites do this to investigate; they have no hands, so they nudge and test things with their mouths to figure out what they are. It never attacked, but it wouldn't leave either, shadowing the boat until they finally started the engine. The crew said the scariest part was how silent it was. So what was it actually waiting for?",
